title: Lithium ion battery comprising lithium ion exchanged zeolite particles

abstract: An electrochemical cell of a secondary lithium ion battery includes lithium ion-exchanged zeolite particles or "lithiated zeolite particles" disposed along at least a portion of a lithium ion transport channel through the electrochemical cell. The lithiated zeolite particles may be disposed within lithium ion transport channels through the electrochemical cell, for example, by being distributed throughout the electrolyte disposed between opposing front surfaces of the negative and positive electrodes. Additionally or alternatively, the lithiated zeolite particles may be disposed within lithium ion transport channels through the electrochemical cell by being distributed throughout the anode, cathode, and/or porous separator sandwiched between opposing front surfaces of the anode and cathode or deposited as a coating on these components.
claims: 2. The electrochemical cell of claim 1, comprising a porous separator, wherein the porous separator is disposed between the opposing front surfaces of the anode and the cathode and is impregnated with the electrolyte.
3. The electrochemical cell of claim 2, wherein the lithiated zeolite particles are further associated with the porous separator.
4. The electrochemical cell of claim 2, wherein the lithiated zeolite particles are further distributed throughout the porous separator.

5. The electrochemical cell of claim 2, wherein the lithiated zeolite particles are further coated on a first side of the porous separator facing the negative electrode, on an opposite second side of the porous separator facing the positive electrode, or on both the first and second sides of the porous separator.

6. The electrochemical cell of claim 2, wherein the separator comprises a first layer and a second layer adjacent to the first layer, and wherein the lithiated zeolite particles are further distributed along an interface between the first layer and the second layer.

7. The electrochemical cell of claim 1, wherein the lithiated zeolite particles are further distributed throughout the negative electrode, the positive electrode, or both the negative and positive electrodes.

8. The electrochemical cell of claim 1, wherein the lithiated zeolite particles are further coated on the front surface of the negative electrode, the front surface of the positive electrode, or both the negative and positive electrodes.

9. The electrochemical cell of claim 1, comprising a negative current collector adjacent the negative electrode and a positive current collector adjacent the positive electrode, and wherein the lithiated zeolite particles are further disposed on a surface of the negative current collector or the positive current collector, or on a surface of both the negative current collector and the positive current collector.
